tip.text: Pork ribs were not too fantastic on it's own, but tastes good with the chili sauce. I suggest going for the Holy Crab spaghetti instead. Other dishes were disappointing.
Too much foam for cafe latte. Prolly americano will be a better choice here!
Food is good but way too pricey, unreasonable. Even charge RM2 for a small bottle of water. Sauce is sweet. They actually have a board telling staff what to 'push' to customers. Be warned!

formattedAddress: 2, Jalan 20/70A, Desa Sri Hartamas (Jalan Sri Hartamas 22)

tip.text: Fish & chips was horrible. Fish overcooked & had fishy smell. Fries was tasteless, felt like eating just calories. Mushroom soup still ok.

formattedAddress: 72A, Jalan Tasik Utama 7 (Medan Niaga Tasik Damai)

tip.text: Food is still ok, just overpriced. Can take quite long to serve. Staff are courteous. They accidentally charged for plates which we didn't take, so do check your bill. Limited choices on the belt.
Baked Egg Pan - this was good! The bread was awesome...top it with the ingredients in the pan.
Acme Breakfast Club - overpriced. Hash brown and poached eggs were good, the rest were meh. The sauteed mushroom wasn't good. (Heard the turkey breast is a better choice)
Tastes good, but expensive. Try the 8 flavor pork.
Mixed sashimi @ RM28 - imho not worth it. No satisfaction.

formattedAddress: 4-2, Jalan Telok Gadong (Off Jalan Klang Lama)

tip.text: Soft shell crab maki is good! Quality may vary sometimes.

formattedAddress: 4-2, Jalan Telok Gadong (Off Jalan Klang Lama)

tip.text: RM1.60/roll of chee cheong fun & RM1/item. This plate costs RM9.60. Way too pricey, taste is below expectation too.
Coleslaw felt a little stale with too much mayonnaise (which actually helped to cover up the stale taste). Lamb chop edible, but not recommended.
Soup base for Tsukemen is really salty but the chunks of pork tasted really good while the chasu was hard - overcooked. Musashi Ramen (spicy base) is good. Don't miss the egg! Gyoza tasted ok.

formattedAddress: Isetan Food Place (1 Utama Shopping Centre)

tip.text: Toro salmon sashimi was just so so. Soft shell crab in the spider roll was not good either. Staff not very attentive. Overall, slightly below expectations considering the rave reviews here.
Good food for spicy lovers! Coupled with good service, this place is recommended.

formattedAddress: 1-47, The Scott Garden (289 Jalan Kelang Lama)

tip.text: Total madhouse on 31st. Beware...while the crowd is large there's also a couple of staff looking lost and directionless...

formattedAddress: 46, Ground & 1st Floor, Jalan Radin Tengah (Sri Petaling)

tip.text: Overall taste was ok, in fact the clear soup base was quite nice. But very oily. Anyway, still a far cry from the original Szechuan steamboat.
Black sesame paste was burnt. Yea burnt!  F-a-i-l-e-d.

formattedAddress: UGK-01, Upper Ground Floor, Paradigm Mall, No. 1, Jalan SS 7/26A, Kelana Jaya (Lot UGK01, Upper Ground Floor)

tip.text: Assorted egg loaf is good. Xiao long bao quality not so consistent. Avoid drunken chicken, horrible...
Cosy ambience, nice concept, food failed. Tasteless hash brown. The rest still passable.
Claypot chicken rice tasted like it was just rice with sauce. It probably was cooked separately and placed in the claypot, and not really cooked on the claypot. Avoid this dish.

venue.name: The Olde Smokehouse Tea Room And Restaurant

tip.text: Try the strawberry coffee here! Chicken deli cheese sandwich toast is simple but delicious. Avoid the strawberry tart though.
Duck noodle (soup base) is good. Wantan noodle was tasteless, but the wantan was awesome. Lots of ajinomoto in soup though...wu kok overrated. Service slow but staff were polite.
